product_name: L'OrealAge Perfect Cell Renewal Midnight Eye Cream
summary: SummaryL'Oréal Paris Age Perfect Cell Renewal Midnight Eye Cream is formulated with antioxidants for visible results on 8 signs of eye aging. Reveal visibly lifted, younger looking eyes.
details: DetailsBenefitsBeauty Sleep in a Jar - Cell Renewal Midnight Eye Opener comforts the delicate eye area for visible results on 8 signs of eye aging. Reveal Visibly Lifted, Younger Looking Eyes.How it Works - Midnight Eye Cream is formulated with dermatologist-recommended Antioxidants and Vitamin E to help support skin's natural renewal process and recover the eye area at night when it is most receptive to repair.What is Unique - Midnight Eye Opener has a Sleep Silk formula that creates the optimal environment for eye area recovery. The lightweight, non-greasy anti-aging eye cream melts in to skin, infusing it with Antioxidants.Immediately, eye contour feels comforted and eye area looks firmer and smooth. Over time, eye area appears more radiant, wrinkles are smoothed, bags and dark circles appear reduced.Effective on all skin types and tones, Dermatologist tested for safety. Suitable for sensitive skin and eyes. Contact Lens Suitable.Key IngredientsAntioxidants help to prevent aging and support skin's natural renewal process. Vitamin E, an essential nutrient present in the skin, helps to reinforce skin's moisture barrier.Item 2629902How To UseTap Midnight Eye Opener around eye contour and lids as first step of your routine. Follow with Midnight Serum and Midnight Cream.IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Dimethicone, Glycerin, Isohexadecane, Alcohol Denat., Butyrospermum Parkii Butter / Shea Butter, Squalane, Cetyl Alcohol, Stearic Acid, Palmitic Acid, Glyceryl Stearate, PEG-100 Stearate, PEG-20 Stearate, Saccharomyces/Xylinum/Black Tea Ferment, Cera Alba / Beeswax / Cire Dabeille, Octyldodecanol, Hydrolyzed Soy Protein, Acetyl Tetrapeptide-9, Adenosine, Caffeine, Capryloyl Salicylic Acid, Secale Cereale Seed Extract / Rye Seed Extract, Sodium Hyaluronate, Sodium Hydroxide, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Tocopherol, Silica, Silica [Nano] / Silica, CI 77891 / Titanium Dioxide, Citric Acid, C13-14 Isoalkane, Glycine Soja Oil / Soybean Oil, Laureth-7, Mica, Myristic Acid, Pentylene Glycol, Polyacrylamide, Tin Oxide, Dimethiconol, CI 16035 / Red 40, CI 19140 / Yellow 5, Chlorhexidine Digluconate, Chlorphenesin, Phenoxyethanol, Potassium Sorbate, Sodium Benzoate (F.I.L. N70029973/1).
how_to_use: Tap Midnight Eye Opener around eye contour and lids as first step of your routine. Follow with Midnight Serum and Midnight Cream.

media.headline: LET the CROWS FLY!
media.caption: Not afraid of MIDNIGHT EYE OPENER!

faceoff_positive.comments: I was happy to try Loreal Midnight Eye Opener cream. I've got dark circles, a little above eye sagging and tiny lines forming around my eyes. I've tried a lot of different products. I often end up with redness or dry patches. One might help one issue, but I'm left with no improvement to my other problems. To find a cream that covers all the bases is great. I use other Loreal products, as well, so I trust them. This cream has been ophthalmologist tested, of course, and it's free of junk ingredients you don't want to be putting on your face. It's light and easy to dab around eyes. It doesn't take a lot of product. I've been using it morning and night for around 3 weeks or so. I've experienced zero redness, zero dry patches. The first thing I noticed is that there's no stinky smell. In fact, I don't smell it at all. I'm big on scent. I can't use products that smell bad for long. It instantly brightens which is fantastic. It cuts my dark circles right down, and I need only apply a little concealer to the inner corners. After a couple weeks of use I noticed my creases, I guess you'd say, are a tiny bit  less droopy. I see more lid now. I've never noticed that using other products, and I've tried many, like I said. My eyes really do look better, and I'm hoping to see even more results with continued use. It's definitely helping with sagging and dark circles. I'm hoping my lines will diminish over time, as well. I was given this product to try in exchange for my honest review. This is an honest review. It really works. Give it a try. It just might end your search for a good eye cream.
faceoff_positive.headline: Seeing real improvements

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received the L'Oréal midnight eye cream for free in exchange for writing an honest review. My initial impression is that I love that it has an iridescent look to it. It went on quite smoothly. Slightly on the thicker side. I'd say it's creamy in texture. It's in scented which is probably best for the masses but I am someone who loves a good scent in my face products. I do love the pearly, shimmery look of it after it's been applied.

I've been using the cream twice a day - once in the morning and once at night. I would have said without the pictures as evidence that I didn't notice a change but I do think there's a slight change noticeable in the pictures I took. On April 8, my eyes looked puffy and red. After using the cream regularly for almost a month, I think my under eyes look slightly less puffy but definitely smoother and less red. I really needed to see the evidence in the pictures to see that there is, in fact, a slight difference. I wouldn't say it's hugely noticeable but there is perhaps a minor change. I had been hoping for more of a noticeable and dramatic difference and less puffiness below my eyes, but I am pleased that it looks more moisturized and smoother. That's the biggest difference I noticed. I don't think it's all that different from other products I've tried, but I've also never taken pictures of a before and after to actually see changes from an eye cream I've used. 

I don't think I'd recommend this product over another eye cream because the before and after difference isn't that remarkable, but I did like the shimmery effect it has after you put it on. I wish the iridescent look lasted longer than about 5 minutes, but I liked how it looked until it disappeared.
faceoff_negative.headline: Had high hopes but didn't make a huge difference
